    "goal_understanding": "The goal of the game is to navigate through a series of grid-based levels, adjusting your carried piece's shape, color, and rotation by stepping on modifier tiles, to match the requirements of goal cells and then step onto them to complete each level. The ultimate aim is to complete all levels without running out of lives.",
    "mechanics_understanding": "The player moves a piece on a grid. The piece has a shape (0-5), a color (orange, blue, green, red, cycling in that order), and a rotation (0\u00b0, 90\u00b0, 180\u00b0, 270\u00b0, wrapping). Each move costs 1 stamina; when stamina hits 0, a life is lost and stamina is reset to its maximum value. Losing all lives ends the game. Special tiles modify the piece: shape modifiers cycle the shape, color modifiers cycle the color, and rotation modifiers rotate the piece 90\u00b0 clockwise. Goal cells activate only when the piece's shape, color, and rotation exactly match the goal's requirements. Stepping on an activated goal completes it. Walls block movement, and the game provides a list of blocked directions each turn to avoid invalid moves."
